label: PLAN
description: This field indicates which Analysis Plan group in the Analysis Plan Parameters is associated with this record.

label: STATEMENTDATE
description: The Statement Cutoff Processing batch program sets this field to the current system date then creates a new Share Analysis record for the selected group that has the counters set to 0.

label: STATEMENTGROUP
description: The information in this record can be used for fee posting and producing analysis statements for the specified statement groups.

label: STATEMENTPREVDATE
description: The information in this record can be used for fee posting and producing analysis statements for the specified statement group.

label: CASHAMTTOTAL
description: This field stores the monthly total of CD, CR, ATM, FR and FD transactions on analyzed accounts.

label: RECORDCHANGEDATE
description: This field stores the system date in the Record Change Date field when you create, change, or save the Share Analysis record.

label: LOCATOR
description: This field value in each record is unique for each member account.

label: COUNTER:1
description: This counter is used to track teller deposit (transactions using the SD transaction code) and batch deposit transactions.

label: COUNTER:2
description: This counter is used to track teller deposit transactions with adjustments.

label: COUNTER:3
description: This counter is used to track returned deposits.

label: COUNTER:4
description: This counter is used to track draft transactions (transactions using the DR transaction code, DRAFTPOST, ACHPOST, ON US, etc.).

label: COUNTER:5
description: This counter is used to track bulk deposits (transactions using the BK transaction code).

label: COUNTER:6
description: This counter is used to track the number of change orders.

label: COUNTER:7
description: This counter is used to track the number of NSF batch postings.

label: COUNTER:8
description: This counter is used to track the number of sweep count transactions.

label: COUNTER:9
description: This counter is used to track the number of stop payment transactions (SP transaction code, audio, home banking).

label: COUNTER:10
description: This counter is used to track the number of account printouts.

label: COUNTER:11
description: This counter is used to track the number of statement balances.

label: COUNTER:12
description: This counter is used to track statement balances.

label: COUNTER:13
description: This counter is used to track check copies.

label: COUNTER:14
description: This counter is used to track checks disbursed from the primary printer (transactions using the KD and KS transaction codes).

label: COUNTER:15
description: This counter is used to track checks disbursed from the secondary printer (transactions using the KO and KS transaction codes).

label: COUNTER:16
description: This counter is used to track money order transactions (transactions using the MO transaction code).

label: COUNTER:17
description: This counter is used to track incoming wire transfers.

label: COUNTER:18
description: This counter is used to track outgoing wire transfers.

label: COUNTER:19
description: This counter is used to track transfers to cover overdrafts (batch postings).

label: COUNTER:20
description: This counter is used to track courtesy pay transactions.

label: COUNTER:21
description: This counter is used to track ACH debits when they post.

label: COUNTER:22
description: This counter is used to track ACH credits when they post.

label: COUNTER:23
description: This counter is used to track ACH debits when you run ACH Origination.

label: COUNTER:24
description: This counter is used to track ACH credits when you run ACH Origination.

label: COUNTER:25
description: This counter is used to track checks received and checks cashed (transactions using the KR and KC transaction codes).

label: COUNTER:26
description: This counter is used to track on-us items drawn on an analyzed share and disbursed from an account (transactions using the ON transaction code).

label: COUNTER:27
description: This counter is used to track lob visits (teller transactions).

label: COUNTER:28
description: This counter is used to track loose coin bulk deposits (transactions using the BK transaction code).

label: COUNTER:29
description: This counter is used to track rolled coin bulk deposits (transactions using the BK transaction code).

label: COUNTER:30
description: This counter is used to track loose currency bulk deposits (transactions using the BK transaction code).

label: COUNTER:31
description: This counter is used to track strapped currency bulk deposits (transactions using the BK transaction code).

label: COUNTER:32
description: This counter is used to track on-us items drawn on a different account and deposited to an analyzed share (transactions using the ON transaction code).

label: COUNTER:33
description: These counters are reserved for future use.
